(Atho Emissions and Fee Routing Policy) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Date: 2026-03-27) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This document defines active monetary policy and fee routing under current consensus constants.) Tj
T*
(- Accounting Units) Tj
T*
(- All consensus accounting is integer-atom based.) Tj
T*
(- 1 ATHO = 1,000,000,000 atoms.) Tj
T*
(- Reward Schedule \(Current\)) Tj
T*
(- Block time target: 120 seconds.) Tj
T*
(- Blocks/year: 262,800.) Tj
T*
(- Era size: 1,314,000 blocks \(5 years\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Pre-tail eras:) Tj
T*
(- Era 1: 10.0 ATHO/block) Tj
T*
(- Era 2: 5.0 ATHO/block) Tj
T*
(- Era 3: 2.5 ATHO/block) Tj
T*
(- Era 4: 1.25 ATHO/block) Tj
T*
(- Era 5: 0.625 ATHO/block) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Transition:) Tj
T*
(- 0.3125 ATHO/block until exact pre-tail target supply reaches 30,000,000 ATHO.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Tail:) Tj
T*
(- Tail reward 0.25 ATHO/block from height 21,102,000 onward.) Tj
T*
(- Tail annual issuance: 65,700 ATHO/year.) Tj
T*
(- Active Fee Policy) Tj
T*
(Current constants:) Tj
T*
(- FEE_PER_BYTE_ATOMS = 225 \(policy unit is vsize\)) Tj
T*
(- MIN_TRANSACTION_FEE_ATOMS = 150,000) Tj
T*
(- DUST_LIMIT_ATOMS = 250) Tj
T*
(- Max block base cap: 2,500,000 bytes) Tj
T*
(- Max block weight: 10,000,000) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Fee routing:) Tj
T*
(- 20% of total fees route to consensus pool.) Tj
T*
(- Remaining 80% are routed through burn/miner split logic.) Tj
T*
(- At tail, routed non-pool fees are burn-targeted \(100% burn policy\), clipped by supply-floor) Tj
T*
(headroom.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Supply floor:) Tj
T*
(- Effective circulating supply is clipped to never go below 21,000,000 ATHO.) Tj
T*
(- No Fixed Base Transaction Size Assumption) Tj
T*
(Atho does **not** use one static tx size for economics or TPS planning. Real size depends on:) Tj
T*
(- input/output counts,) Tj
T*
(- varint widths,) Tj
T*
(- witness lengths,) Tj
T*
(- optional metadata.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Representative estimates \(compressed witness, metadata empty\):) Tj
T*
(- 1 in / 1 out: ~513 vB) Tj
T*
(- 1 in / 2 out: ~566 vB) Tj
